CAPE TOWN – Cape Town Mayor Patricia de Lille on Thursday said she is not a sangoma and cannot predict if she will remain with the Democratic Alliance (DA) in future should she be removed from her post. Her comments come just a day after she lost an internal vote of no-confidence by the Cape Town city caucus. READ: Patricia de Lille loses vote “I’m not a sangoma, I can’t see into the future,” de Lille said when asked about her future with the DA. “What I know is I will work hard to clear my name.” “It’s about my reputation... My name was smeared in public,” the mayor said. De Lille said at the 25 community meetings she attended in the past month, not one person asked her to resign. “I’m a fighter for justice and fairness,” she added. For the full interview, click on the video above. eNCA